# training/data/
#
# This directory holds labelled training and evaluation data.
# It is intentionally excluded from version control via .gitignore
# (real datasets may contain PII or be too large for git).
#
# Expected file conventions:
#
#   train_*.csv   — Training data (used by training/train.py)
#   test_*.csv    — Held-out evaluation data (used by training/evaluate.py)
#
# Required CSV format (header row mandatory):
#
#   text,label
#   "This product is wonderful!",1
#   "Completely disappointed.",0
#
#   label: 1 = POSITIVE, 0 = NEGATIVE
#
# How to populate for a real retrain:
#   1. Export labelled examples to train_v2.csv and test_v2.csv
#   2. Place them in this directory
#   3. Open a PR — the retrain.yml workflow fires automatically
#      on any change to training/data/**
#
# If no CSV files are present, train.py and evaluate.py fall back
# to a small synthetic dataset so the CI pipeline can always run.
# Synthetic data is only suitable for pipeline validation, not
# real model quality assessment.
